{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox dam | name = Sempor Dam | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Indonesia | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | location_map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|7|33|59.78|S|109|29|10.12|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Indonesia | location = [[Gombong|District Gombong]], [[Kebumen Regency|Kebumen]], [[Central Java|Central Java Province]] | purpose = Power, water supply, flood control, recreation | status = O | construction_began = 1967 | opening = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1978}} | demolished = | cost = | owner = | dam_type = Embankment, rock-fill | dam_crosses = Sempor River | dam_length = | dam_height = {{Convert|58|m|ft|abbr=on}} | dam_height_foundation= | dam_height_thalweg = | dam_elevation_crest = | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = | spillway_count = | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | res_name = | res_capacity_total = {{Convert|56900000|m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_catchment = | res_surface = {{Convert|43|km2|mi2|abbr=on}} | res_max_length = | res_max_width = | res_max_depth = | res_elevation = | res_tidal_range = | plant_name = | plant_coordinates = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = 1978 | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_turbines = 1&nbsp;×&nbsp;1 MW [[Francis-type]] | plant_hydraulic_head = | plant_capacity = 1 MW | plant_annual_gen = | website = | extra = }} '''Sempor Dam''' is an [[embankment dam]] on the Sempor River in [[Gombong|District Gombong]], [[Kebumen Regency|Kebumen]], [[Central Java|Central Java Province]], [[Republic of Indonesia]].<ref name="travel.detik2013">{{cite web|url=http://travel.detik.com/read/2013/07/02/152000/2241743/1025/waduk-sempor-di-gombong-tak-kalah-cantik-dengan-jatiluhur|title=Waduk Sempor di Gombong, Tak Kalah Cantik dengan Jatiluhur|author=Mukhammad Najib|publisher=travel.detik.com|year=2013|accessdate=12 May 2014|language=id}}</ref><ref name="travel.detik2012">{{cite web|url=http://travel.detik.com/read/2012/08/23/151500/1993070/1025/waduk-sempor-kesejukan-di-tengah-panasnya-kebumen|title=Waduk Sempor, Kesejukan di Tengah Panasnya Kebumen|author=Markus Sugeng Budhi Prasetyo|publisher=travel.detik.com|year=2012|accessdate=12 May 2014|language=id}}</ref> In addition to being a tourist attraction Sempor Dam is a source of [[irrigation]] water for farmers.<ref name="kebumenkab">{{cite web|url=http://www.kebumenkab.go.id/index.php/public/potenda/detail/8|title=Waduk Sempor|author=|publisher=Pemerintah Kabupaten Kebumen|year=2012|accessdate=12 May 2014}}</ref> It helps irrigate thousands of [[paddy fields]] in the delta.<ref name="kebumenkab"/> It also provides for flood control and has a 1 MW [[hydroelectric]] power station at its base. Construction on the dam started in 1967 but in the same year water from flash floods over-topped it, causing the dam to fail on November 29, 1967. The wave of water killed 160 people in three towns, including [[Magelang]]. <ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=gL9scSG3K_gC&dat=19671202&printsec=frontpage&hl=en "138 Known Dead As Dam Collapses"], ''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette'', December 2, 1967, p1</ref> <ref>"Deaths at Dam up to 160", ''St. Louis Post-Dispatch'', December 3, 1967, p1</ref> and delivered widespread damage to the area.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://ceae.colorado.edu/~amadei/CVEN5768/PDF/Damfailure.pdf | title=Dam Failure | publisher=Colorado University | date=28 August 2002 | accessdate=14 May 2014 | author=Christian, John T.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/?id=zuqibWGc3-MC&pg=PA338&lpg=PA338&dq=sempor+dam+fatalities#v=onepage&q=sempor%20dam%20fatalities&f=false | title=Mountain Rivers Revisited | publisher=John Wiley & Sons | author=Wohl, Ellen | year=2013 | pages=338 | isbn=1118671562}}</ref> Construction later restarted on the dam and it was completed in 1978. Its power station was later commissioned in 1980.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://repit.files.wordpress.com/2013/03/gbu-ip-plta-mrica-pb-sudirman.pdf | title=Mrica HEPP | publisher=Indonesia Power – Generation Business Unit | accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.fao.org/nr/water/aquastat/countries_regions/index.stm | title=Countries, regions, transboundary river basins (Search 'Indonesia' and 'dams') | publisher=United Nations FAO | accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref>
